RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 1 6 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 36300. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAGIC TOMAHAWK settled on the rail in midfield down the backstretch, improved inside through the turn, was looking for running room behind the leaders straightening out for the drive, angled out, bullying his way through in the five path at the sixteenth pole and surged late to get the victory. CELENTANO was unhurried having one foe beaten down the backside, improved passing horses outside at the three furlong pole, weaved between runners smartly with a quarter to run, burst between rivals in the four path in upper stretch, took command briefly with an eighth to go but could not fend off the charging winner in the final strides. FIGHTING IRISH was coaxed early on down the backstretch to stay in touch with the field, began to pick up rivals four wide at the quarter pole, shifted out for clear run in the eight path at the furlong marker and closed with a rush but could not get there in time. TREBUCHET had a good trip nestled behind the engaged trio throughout the turn, rallied up the fence in upper stretch and finished up with intent, closing in, but unfortunately was on the losing end of a three way photo for the place share. TODAY travelled in mid-pack four deep down the backside, started to rally five wide being floated out at the quarter pole, was in range of the leaders in the eight path turning for home, battled on stubbornly to the wire but needed a little more late to pose a threat at the finish. WHADDYA MEAN watched the contesting trio battle four wide down the backside, took closer order to the leaders four wide through the turn, angled out to the seven path for the drive to the finish line with a chance for a piece of the prize, fought gamely between others at the furlong pole but gave way losing his path in deep stretch. MIAH SAID prompted the pace with runners on each side down the back straight, continued to argue for the lead between foes around the turn, was still in the mix three wide at the top of the lane but yielded in the final furlong. ABSOLUTE CHAIRMAN had a slim advantage three deep outside down the backstretch, battled for the lead three wide through the turn, was in range in the five path in upper stretch, had to be steadied losing his lane at the sixteenth pole between horses and could not recover to pose a threat. CADFAEL pressed the pace inside down the backstretch, dueled on the rail up front around the bend, could not find more turning for home and was engulfed by rivals on either side at the furlong marker. JUST FOR MADDIE broke in at the start, was checked mildly between foes at the three eighths pole, made no headway on others through the turn and could no be a presence in the stretch drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 3 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 77. Claiming Purse 54500. FOR TWO YEAR OLDS. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since October 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL HUDSON had a good position outside tracking the contesting duo down the backstretch, patiently began to reel in the leaders into the turn, pounced to the lead three wide at the quarter pole and continued to fight on up front down the lane just holding off numerous runners at the wire for the win. DESTINY RO could see this field down the backstretch, started to reach for more ground passing foes on the rail at the quarter pole, shifted to the three path to be in the hunt at the top of the stretch, weaved in and out looking for path down the lane and just missed timing the final surge for the win at the wire. CANTUCCI travelled in the third flight on the inside in the early stages, moved in smartly at the three furlong marker to be a menacing presence four wide at the quarter pole and ran on willingly between horses in deep stretch to just save show at the finish line. RED SNEAKERS was unhurried ahead of one rival down the backstretch, closed the gap on the tiring leaders with three eighths left to run, loomed five wide at the top of the lane and finished up mildly inching closer at the wire. BAR TALK was steadied on the start, stalked on the outside in the third flight down the back straight, was asked for more three furlongs from home, offered little response on the turn, shifted out six wide for the drive and gaining quickly on the leaders in the final furlong but ran out of room. RED ENSIGN broke outwards on the start, tracked on the rail down the backside, was roused at the three furlong pole but could not go on with others making a run and was one paced on the rail in the stretch drive. COMPUTER HACKER veered out on the break, recovered to hound the leader outside in the first turn, forced the pace outside down the backstretch, chased in vain on the final turn and emptied out turning for home. VALYRIAN SKY cleared to the rail leading this pack into the first turn, set a brisk pace while shadowed outside down the back straight, was collared outside at the quarter pole, had nothing left to give and faltered in upper stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: RY PIE had a nice position watching the top two going into the turn, was patiently nestled behind on the rail waiting for his cue, burst up the fence to seize control at the two furlong pole and was kept to the task down the lane to hold rivals at bay comfortably crossing the line. CALLYOUBACKINFIVE bobbled soon after the start to trail down the backside, closed the gap travelling three wide between rivals on the turn, shifted six wide for the drive but could not get involved through the lane. PERSEVERE broke inwards at the start, stalked outside near the back down the backside, made no impact two wide between running on the turn and lacked a rally in the stretch to the wire. QURBAAN'S KINGDOM stalked near the rear in the early going, made little impression inside foes around the bend and could not be a factor running to the finish line. ASHUKA co-trailed three deep outside at the half, made a brief turn of foot rallying four wide improving around horses through the turn but could not offer much in the stretch drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 7 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 85. Claiming Purse 23700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE DECEMBER 15, 2022. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THREE SONNY SIDEUP tracked in the second flight down the backside, angled out off the tiring early leaders to loom four wide turning for home, bumped fellow rival when set down at the furlong pole dueling for the lead and under left handed encouragement drifted out late to hold on for the win a photo. COACH ABERNATHY travelled on the rail in mid-pack in the early going, stalked all alone in the third flight down the backstretch, shifted outside closing the gap quickly three wide at the quarter pole, bid for the lead five wide at the top of the stretch, exchanged bumps with inside rival driving to the wire at the eighth pole and lost the battle for the win while being pushed out late by the winner nearing the finish line. MISTER MESEEKS stalked near the back of the pack saving ground in the first turn, advanced mildly on the fence down the back straight, was urged for more with five sixteenths to go, angled outside in the five path with run straightening out for home and closed outside, smartly going by runners late but could not threaten the top two at the wire and settled for a clear third in the end. TOURIST'S DREAM was bumped at the start, clipped heels going into the first turn, began to inch closer to the leaders while in hand inside at the quarter pole and rallied late to close in for a minor share in the end. BAYTOWN ELVIS broke in at the start, had a mild lead in the first turn, bobbed heads for the lead running inside down the backstretch, fought on for the lead on the rail turning for home, could not find more late and tired at the sixteenth pole. SOCIETY JOE prompted the pace outside on the first turn, continued to hound the leader outside down the backstretch, still battled up front in upper stretch but weakened between rivals in the last sixteenth. SEVENTYSEVEN STONE was allowed to settle on the fence trailing in the early parts of the race, started to gain some run on the rail on the final turn and had good late energy inside to pass some rivals down the stretch. MUSKOKA GIANT was brushed inside at the start, stared to gain on others outside four deep down the backside, put in a brief run four wide circling at the three furlong pole, angled out in the six path at the top of the lane, could not go on and flattened out in mid-stretch. SILENT LUCIDITY was brushed outside on the break, stalked near the back with runners on either side down the backstretch, made a mild run four wide on the final turn but could not play a role running down the stretch. KODIAK MAMBA (IRE) was tucked in on the rail behind the leaders for most of the race, was in range just behind the fading early leaders turning for home but could not offer a finish in deep stretch to pose a threat in the end. KITTEN'S BOY stalked three wide near the rear in the first turn, could not gain on rivals down the backstretch, angled out widest in the eight path for the drive to the line but could not get into contention running to the wire. THUNDERHEAVYRAIN settled on the outside in the third flight early on, made little progression between horses along the backstretch, could not keep up with others midway on the final turn and had nothing to show in the stretch drive.
